title: Matt&#39;s map of interesting things in the woods.
name: Matt's map of interesting things in the woods.
description: This is a map I created for a school assignment.  it includes abandoned and interesting things I found over the years and the woods.

properties.name: Amotol Raceway
properties.description: this is the location of the Amotol Raceway built 1926.  The track was a steeply banked 1.5 mile long and 50' wide oval.  The board track was built to handle speeds of 160 MPH.  The construction required 4.5 million board feet of lumber, enough to fill 253 railroad cars.   A 50' wide dirt track was built as an "apron" on the inner side of the board track.      More info at http://amatol.atlantic.edu/speedway_menu.html

properties.name: Circus drive-in  (abandoned)
properties.description: this area used to be the circus drive in.  This theater opened in 1953 with a capacity of 1000 cars.  It closed in 1979.  Currently the area is very overgrown with the screen still standing.  more info at:http://www.drive-ins.com/theater/njtcirc

properties.name: Winslow Junction
properties.description: the Winslow Junction was once a very busy railroad junction.  Currently this site is owned by the Southern Railroad of New Jersey. avoid walking around unannounced as there is an employee living in the caboose on the siding that parallels spring road. if you want to look at the trains ask permission from someone in the shop on Spring Road the people there are friendly.

properties.name: abandoned quarry
properties.description: this area is now owned by New Jersey Fish and wildlife.

properties.name: old halfway ( hidden Lakes)
properties.description: this lakes used to be a clay mines.  I believe that Clay was used at the Pasadena terra-cotta factory.  This area is patrolled by New Jersey Fish and wildlife rangers.
